title._content: A lady on skis in Gysinge, Gästrikland, Sweden

description._content: Esther Isabel Seaver Burno (1903-1965) on skis in Gysinge. She was a Professor of Art History. Former director of Dayton Art Institute in Ohio, USA, and head of the Fine Arts Division at Wheaton College in Norton, Massachusetts. Doctor's degree at Radcliff College in Cambridge, Massachusetts, USA. Also a former student at Stockholm University (where she probably got to know Berit Wallenberg). Esther Isabel Seaver Burno (1903-1965) på skidor i Gysinge. Hon var professor i konsthistoria. Tidigare chef för Dayton Konstmuseum i Ohio, USA, samt chef för konstavdelningen på Wheaton College i Norton, Massachusetts. Doktorsexamen vid Radcliff College i Cambridge, Massachusetts, USA. Också tidigare studerande vid Stockholms universitet (där hon troligen blev bekant med Berit Wallenberg). Parish (socken): Österfärnebo Province (landskap): Gästrikland Municipality (kommun): Sandviken County (län): Gävleborg Photograph by: Berit Wallenberg Date: 04.02.1929 Format: Film Persistent URL: kmb.raa.se/cocoon/bild/show-image.html?id=16001000070344 Read more about the photo database (in english): www.kms.raa.se/cocoon/bild/about.html
